title: Milica Mijatović
text:
Milica Mijatović (born 26 June 1991) is a <a href="Serbia">Serbia</a>n <a href="women%27s%20soccer">football</a> <a href="Striker%20%28association%20football%29">striker</a> currently playing for <a href="BK%20H%C3%A4cken%20%28women%29">BK Häcken</a> in the <a href="Damallsvenskan">Damallsvenskan</a>. She previously played for <a href="%C5%BDFK%20Crvena%20zvezda">Red Star Belgrade</a> in the <a href="Prva%20%C5%BEenska%20liga">Serbian 1st League</a>, <a href="SFK%202000">SFK Sarajevo</a> in the <a href="Bosnian%20women%27s%20football%20championship">Bosnian Zenska Liga</a>, and <a href="Melbourne%20City%20FC%20%28W-League%29">Melbourne City</a> in the Australian <a href="W-League%20%28Australia%29">W-League</a>. In August 2012 she made her debut in the <a href="UEFA%20Women%27s%20Champions%20League">Champions League</a> with <a href="BIIK%20Kazygurt">BIIK Kazygurt</a>.
Club career.
Mijatović signed prior to the <a href="2019%E2%80%9320%20W-League">2019–20 W-League</a> season for <a href="Melbourne%20City%20FC%20%28W-League%29">Melbourne City</a> where she was a vital player scoring 7 goals when the club finished the season unbeaten and as champions.
In September 2020, Mijatović joined <a href="Apollon%20Ladies%20F.C.">Apollon Limassol</a> on a short term contract to play 2 games in UEFA Champions League.
International career.
Mijatović is a member of the <a href="Serbia%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Serbian national team</a>.
